node.text: Telling our friends and family our pregnancy news has been hands down one of the most special parts of this experience so far 🤍🤰🏼!! From my mom and dad on FaceTime the second I found out to more planned out reveals at the end of the first trimester, getting to share this news with our loved ones has been one of the highlights of our lives. We didn’t film everyone we told, because a lot of the time I got so excited I just couldn’t even remember to take out my camera!!!! I.e. most of the people I told in the first few weeks 🤣 But these are incredible moments captured by both me and J, and you’ll see how much my dad got into the news revealing too!! If you know me then you know I am SO GRATEFUL for & obsessed with the people in my life. I feel so ridiculously lucky for these friends who are family, and family who are friends. I LOVE YOU GUYS!!! It’s a longer video and I hope it brings you joyyyy!!! What’s your favorite way we told people?!? 🤍🙏🏻🤰🏼 #pregnancyreveal #pregnancyannouncement #pregnancyjourney #19weekspregnant

node.text: YOU GUYS!! We are so excited to share this moment with you. My parents set up this EPIC scavenger hunt for us to find out the gender of our baby 👶🏼… and it was quite literally the best moment of all time. I don’t think anything will ever top this excitement. It was what we both predicted and knew in our hearts but it was still SHOCKING to find out for real. My parents are the best humans on earth for surprising us in such a creative way. NEVER OVER THIS DAY, this shock, this magic!!!!! BABY A IS A… !!!!!!! #genderreveal #genderrevealparty #pregnancy #bestdayever

node.text: It’s hereee!! The night I told @inspire_people that I’m PREGNANT & that our baby is coming in December! I kept it in for an entire week while he was away 🙊 I still don’t know how I did that. I told him in a few ways, which you’ll see here! One was with our baby Huddy wearing the best bandana ever because duh. Then my camera turned off (ideal timing I know 🤣) but I had him reenact his reaction at the end!! The filming returns with J opening the box full of positive tests!!!! That moment was when the reality REALLY HIT HIM!!!! So happy to share this moment with you guys. The most special night of our lives, hands down. Never over getting to tell the love of my life that he is going to be a DAD! 🤍😭 #babyalbrecht #pregnancyannouncement #pregnancyreveal

node.text: Growing life 🕊 has put things into the ultimate perspective for me. Anything that disturbs my peace no longer gets attention. I protect my joy like a mama bear. The hugest revelation came through last week about who I am and where I’m going, what gets to have my awareness and space and what does not. It’s a powerful feeling, committing to staying aligned at all costs. Stay on your path, and let the law of attraction bring good things to you like a magnet. Living in this state of consciousness more and more now because I am committed, I need to, to stay sane. I am 20 weeks today, so this pregnancy is officially halfway. I’m so grateful for the upleveling of soul self my son is already bringing me. No words. 🤍 #20weekspregnant #soulonfire

node.text: This is your daily reminder to find what sets your soul on fire, and do that. 🤍 Gather the people that make you feel the most alive, and do life with them. Awaken to the moments where you feel like YOU in your truest essence. Be true to yourself at all costs. Life is so much more simple than we make it, and life is always giving us a new moment to find peace. Every day is a new day to find the inner calling within. To walk away from what no longer serves us. To protect our boundaries from what sucks our energy  and makes us feel less at ease. To be aware and in tune with what our hearts have to stay, instead of succumbing to constant distractions. Your soul is always speaking. Will you listen? 🕊 #soulonfire

node.text: Telling our friends and family our pregnancy news has been hands down one of the most special parts of this experience so far 🤍🤰🏼!! From my mom and dad on FaceTime the second I found out to more planned out reveals at the end of the first trimester, getting to share this news with our loved ones has been one of the highlights of our lives. We didn’t film everyone we told, because a lot of the time I got so excited I just couldn’t even remember to take out my camera!!!! I.e. most of the people I told in the first few weeks 🤣 But these are incredible moments captured by both me and J, and you’ll see how much my dad got into the news revealing too!! If you know me then you know I am SO GRATEFUL for & obsessed with the people in my life. I feel so ridiculously lucky for these friends who are family, and family who are friends. I LOVE YOU GUYS!!! It’s a longer video and I hope it brings you joyyyy!!! What’s your favorite way we told people?!? 🤍🙏🏻🤰🏼 #pregnancyreveal #pregnancyannouncement #pregnancyjourney #19weekspregnant

node.text: Thinking so much about the delicate and intense balance of being a light worker on earth right now. This morning my heart broke to hear the news of the passing of a dear teacher & friend @gurujagat - someone who helped introduce me to kundalini yoga and embraced me into the spiritual community with open arms. Some of her first words to me were, “Wow, you kinda look like the girl next store on the outside but you really are so fucking cosmic and powerful. Let me help you harness that. You came here to play big.” 😭🤍 I’ll never forget it. It’s wild, as all weekend was a BIG portal for me and my clear message from above was to root into my purpose, and to live as the spiritual teacher I came here to be. I can get very in my head about this and try to tell myself to just show up online and “act like a normal human” but that’s not me, and I am feeling that really potent reminder big time. I want to thank Guru Jagat for reminding me that I am a powerful cosmic human, we all are, and it’s no longer time to play small. Things are shifting. We came here for a reason. Sending immense love to all of her friends and family and the Rama community — let’s honor her legacy by owning our full light working power. I am inspired to do just that. 🤍🕊 #soulonfire #kundaliniawakening #gurujagat

node.text: Today was the most blessed day, our baby boy’s 120th day ceremony calling in the highest version of his soul. In kundalini, it is said that this day of pregnancy is the day the baby’s soul comes into the mama’s body. The day when his subconscious mind begins to form, and the day the woman becomes mother. All I have to say is wow — I am truly in awe. I am in awe of the love and support we feel surrounding this baby boy already, I am blown away by the sweet friends in our lives who made this last minute celebration out of this world special. The power of this beautiful circle today guided the way for so many visions and visitations from our little spirit son, from his magnetic blue aura to a waterfall of golden light consciousness. Today I also woke up feeling different, way different. Feeling like not only is my life about to change but I am changing. My future vision felt clear. This is the most unreal portal and I am soaking in every moment. Special thanks to my divine soul sister @brittdeanda for making today so special 🌸 and to @tejkaur.khalsa who is truly the kundalini master, what an honor and a gift to have had this day. So grateful, and so filled up. 🤍☁️✨⚡️ Send is your love as the meditations and blessings from this powerful portal will continue through the weekend!! Love you all so much. #babyalbrecht

node.text: On my mind lately: learning to have unshakable boundaries while also not building walls around my spirit. Protecting my heart space and energy, while allowing myself to pour out the contents of my soul in safe spaces. This year has taught me so much of that. The noise in the world is loud, there is not much room left for nuance. Long gone are the days where the internet is a safe space to spill the intricacies of my spirit and all of my daily musings and feelings. But something I’ve come to learn is, that is so okay. It’s HEALTHY. I love reserving bits and pieces of myself for the moments that matter most, for the spaces that feel utterly easeful and close knit. I am committed to listening to my intuition, never letting the outer noise drown out what I know to be true for me. That’s what I want for all of us. Our intuitions are screaming out in all moments, just wanting to be heard. Imagine if just for today, you knew your own power. If just today, you enforced strong boundaries but also left room for the right amount of softness. Firm, but soft. Strong, but open. Aware, but alive. That’s my focus right now. 🤍💭✨ You with me? #soulonfire #tbbmademedoit

node.text: I am getting so excited for our Kauai baby moon in a few weeks!! I’m not sure if it’s hit me yet that by the end of this year we will be a family of four 🙈 including Huddy of course. I cannot wait to see what this little boy will be like, who he will look like, what traits he will take on from each of us. If he is a mini Jonathan my heart will explode. And I am certain I will burst when I get to see the love of my love become a dad, he has had such DAD energy ever since I’ve known him. What I do know is that our son has a special energy about him already. He is calm, wise, grounded. He has forced me to slow down. He has a stubborn and strong mind of his own. I try to connect to his spirit daily. 🤍 I have a new blog post up today all about second trimester musings. I can’t believe that in one week I will be HALFWAY through this pregnancy!! I am soaking in every moment. Any tips from mamas / dads out there to stay present in this surreal experience? #19weekspregnant #babymoon #babyalbrecht

node.text:
Made my creamy AF cauliflower cheesy pasta last night & let’s just say it was a hit! I love sneaking veggies into traditional comfort foods, it makes me feel like a little kid again but with all of the nutrients and nourishing goodness. My passion for making plant based foods delicious runs so deep, I honestly know it’s part of my purpose here on this earth. Plants & spirituality, spirituality & plants. And the HEALING power of plants. They all go so hand in hand to me. I also dream of opening a veg restaurant one day, maybe in malibu… would you come?! Sharing the recipe for this bad boy here, and there is another (even creamier version!!) in my celestial ebook! 🌱

TBB CREAMY AF CAULIFLOWER CHEESE!
1 head of steamed cauliflower 
1 cup low sodium vegetable stock 
1/4 cup + 2 tbsp nutritional yeast 
2-3 tbsp tahini 
1 tbsp Dijon mustard 
Juice of 1 lemon (2 lemons if you want it super zesty!)
1 tsp garlic powder
1 tsp red pepper flake

Blend, and pour over rice pasta (or any gluten free pasta you’d like), mix in some steamed spinach, too with more red pepper flake, and enjoy! Voila!! Will you try this?! #soulonfire #plantbaseddiet #plantbasednutrition #vegancheesesauce

node.text: This journey will never not make me emotional. I feel so beyond blessed and grateful to be carrying our healthy baby boy after being told for so many years that I would never be healthy enough to carry a baby or be a mother. It was debilitating to hear those words over and over again, and it shattered something deep within me. But at a certain point I refused to let them be my reality. Healing from chronic Lyme disease and taking my health into my own hands is my proudest accomplishment in this life. I know it’s hard for many to understand, but in the depths of Lyme I was living my own personal hell - having lost what felt like my present, past, and future. Then I decided to shift my reality, take my power back, and do whatever it possibly took to heal. I never stopped having faith (and my husband didn’t either 😭). Now this healthy body carrying this healthy baby is the pinnacle of HEALTH to me 🌈 and I will share it from the rooftops. We can all heal. We are our own healers. If you are struggling to heal or conceive: I see you, I love you, you are not alone. If I can heal, you can too. This baby is a blessing in so many ways, and most of all I thank his precious little soul for reminding me that I am strong - for giving me my life back. 🤍👼🏼👶🏼 #babyalbrecht #18weekspregnant #lymediseaseawareness

node.text: Celestial bliss bowls on repeat around here with mantra music playing & all of the slow, rainy day coziness. I’ve been curled up on the couch all day catching up on rest & I NEEDED a day like today!! So heavenly. Also, I cannot even tell you how much baby boy has me craving fruit, green juice, smoothies, smoothie bowls - if it’s fruity & vegan, he’s in. This is my all time favorite celestial CHOCO NICE CREAM bowl, made of: 2 ripe frozen bananas, 1/2 cup coconut milk (or almond), 1 tbsp peanut butter, 1 date, 2 tbsp cacao powder, and topped with more dates, crushed dark chocolate, cacao nibs, coco yogurt, & a scoop of coconut butter! Who is going to make this recipe?! I’ll make a reel of it later this week to show you how I make. 🤍🍫🍌 also I love hearing your cravings if you’ve been pregnant- what are yours?! #tbbmademedoit #plantbasedpregnancy #18weekspregnant

node.text: I had the most powerful meditation connecting to my baby boy and the divine mother within this morning. In the stillness I realized that for the first time since before I got sick many years ago, I feel truly at home in my body. These four and a half months of pregnancy have brought new pains and discomforts, but in moving through them I feel fully alive in a way I never did during the Lyme pain. This is an embodied, awakened to my core feeling. Open and raw and untouchable. My intuition is soaring, creativity is flowing, and most of all love is radiating through every moment. I had a vision in this meditation of my baby’s third eye connecting to mine, a radiating pulsing sensation of bright white light. It was the most familiar and powerful thing I’ve ever known. I am in awe of what happens internally during pregnancy, as our bodies become a portal for the divine to flow through. So surrendered & in reverence to this process… & just wanted to share the love with my favorite people when I came back to this realm 🤍 #18weekspregnant #babyalbrecht
